Dear Students,

Greetings from Team Avanti!

About Avanti Fellows

Avanti Fellows is a social enterprise established in March 2010 to help
bright students from lowincome homes gain admission to premier
undergraduate colleges by providing affordable training and mentoring. It
has a well established Students' Chapter in IITMadras with a team of
around 40 mentors and mentor coordinators directly involved in mentoring of
students in Jawahar Navodaya Vidyalaya, Pondicherry.


Avanti Fellows is a Pan IIT Alumni India initiative, winner of the
Stanford BASES Social EChallenge 2010 and recipient of the Echoing Green
and DRK Fellowships 2012.
Call for Interns

Eligibility
Undergraduate students of all years.

Overview of the Role
At JNV Pondicherry, Avanti Fellows has established a learning center to
help 50 students build strong foundations in science & math and prepare for
engineering entrance exams through a technologybased learning program. The
Intern will work directly with our Center Manager to provide academic
support to the students this winter.

There are 2 openings offered

Opening 1:

Duration  Nov 28 to Dec 12

Opening 2: 

Duration  Dec 12 to Dec 26

Note that the above slots are flexible, subject to individual
considerations.

Roles and Responsibilities

The Intern is expected to guide the 12th class students in the last leg of
their JEE Advanced Preparation. This would involve clearing doubts,
discussing exam strategies and teaching topics which the students are
finding difficult in common.

For the 11th class students the Intern must

    Understand each studentE2s academic history and progress till d
ate
    Work with the Center Manager to develop customized study plans for
   each Fellow
    Conduct group doubt solving and concept building academic sessions
    Conduct oneonone academic sessions with each student to provide
   customized support
    Conduct, evaluate and analyze customized Chapter Tests for each Fellow
 as
   necessary


The ideal traits for this role are:

    Selfdriven and motivated
    Strong foundations in high school physics, chemistry and mathematics
    Passionate about teaching
    Excellent communication and interpersonal skills

Duration
A minimum of 6 to 8 hours a day, for 15 days. The Interns can spend more
time with the students if they feel it is required.

Location
Pondicherry (Jawahar Navodaya Vidyalaya, Periya Kalapet)

Compensation
Rs 1,250 per week. Accommodation and food will be provided.


